<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Library management system</title>
    <style>
        table{
            border:solid;
        }
        body{
            background-color: bisque;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#"> About Us</a></li>
                <li><a href="#"> contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
        <h1>Library Manegement System</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Avaliable Books</h2>
        <table style="border: 1px;">
            <tr>
                <th>BookName</th>
                <th>BookAuthor</th>
                <th>BookPrice</th>
                <th>BookPage</th>
                <th>BookState</th>
            </tr>
        <%data.forEach((book)=>{%>
            <tr>
                <td><%=book.bookName%></td>
                <td><%=book.bookAuthor%></td>
                <td><%=book.bookPrice%></td>
                <td><%=book.bookPage%></td>
                <td><%=book.bookState%></td>
                
       <% })%>


    </table>
    
    
    <!-- Add new book -->
     
     <h2>Add new book</h2>

   <form action="/" method="post" >
    <input type="text" placeholder="bookName" name="bookName" required>
    <input type="text" placeholder="bookAuthor" name="bookAuthor" required>
    <input type="text" placeholder="bookPage" name="bookPage" required>
    <input type="text" placeholder="BookPrice" name="bookPrice">
    <input type="submit" value="submit">

   </form>
   <!-- issuing books -->
<form action="/issue" method="post">
    <input type="text" name="bookName" id="" placeholder="Enter Book Name" required>
    <button type="submit" value="bookName">Issue</button>
</form>
<!-- returning books -->
<form action="/return" method="post">
    <input type="text" name="bookName" id="" placeholder="Enter Book Name" required>
    <button type="submit" value="bookName">Return</button>
</form>
<!-- deleting books -->
<form action="/delete" method="post">
    <input type="text" name="bookName" placeholder="Enter Book Name" required>
    <button type="submit" value="bookName">Delete</button>
</form>


    



    </section>
<section id="discription">
   <h3> Library Management System Description</h3>
   <div id="p1">
    <p>The Library Management System is a web-based application designed to manage and organize books efficiently within a
    library. It allows librarians or users to perform key operations such as adding new books, issuing books to users,
    returning issued books, and deleting unavailable or outdated books from the collection.</p>
   </div>
   <div id="p2">
    <p>The system maintains important details for each book, including the book name, author, number of pages, price, and
    current status (Available or Issued). It provides an easy-to-use interface that displays all books in a structured table
    format, ensuring quick access and updates.</p>
   </div>
   <div id="p3">
    <p>This system helps reduce manual work by automating record management and minimizing errors. It also improves efficiency
    by keeping all data centralized, easy to search, and instantly accessible. Overall, the Library Management System
    simplifies the process of handling books and enhances the management of library operations.</p>
   </div>
    
    
</section>
    
